cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SD 

The paper deals with scaling the energy and processing throughput of GEMM and CONV kernels for multimedia applications, which are typically related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves linear projections and optimization techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of ARM Cortex A15 processor, which falls under the sub-category cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Finally, the paper involves optimization of computation, which is relevant to sub-category cs.SD (Software Engineering).
